		<td><b>Microphone Schematics for NES, NES2 and New FC</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I was asked to do a little research into the FC microphone, and how to make it functional on the New Famicom (A/V). In the process, so far, I have <a href="http://www.atariusa.com/Famicom_Schematics/Microphone" class="postlink">whipped up a schematic for the microphone circuitry</a>... 
<br />
<br />The New FC and NES2 use a unified custom IC in place of the 40H368. so for those who want to make the mic work on your system, you'll essentially need to build this using a 40H368, or compatible part. The NES still uses the 40H368, so all I presume that you'd need to do is add the additional circuitry, however, this is (at present) untested and unverified.
<br />
<br />If you find any error in the design, please point it out and feel free to make corrections, suggestions or the usual ridicule as necessary.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
